cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is about video super-resolution using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes an optical flow reconstruction network and uses motion compensation, which involves learning the motion patterns in the video, indicating that machine learning (cs.LG) is also relevant. Additionally, the paper involves image and video processing (cs.MM), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and graphics (cs.GR) in terms of generating high-quality video frames.
